body_html:
Looking at the documentation here:
https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/contrib.layers/higher_level_ops_for_building_neural_network_layers_#convolution2d

  • weight_init is not a keyword, it has to be weights_initializer
  • num_output_channels is not a keyword, maybe you mean num_outputs

Please make sure you read the documentation carefully. Python wont accept any abbreviations or any similar keywords.

Looking at the documentation here:
https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/contrib.layers/higher_level_ops_for_building_neural_network_layers_#convolution2d

- weight_init is not a keyword, it has to be weights_initializer
- num_output_channels is not a keyword, maybe you mean num_outputs

Please make sure you read the documentation carefully. Python wont accept any abbreviations or any similar keywords.
